Test_Case_Name: TC02_Create Locate Request - Emergency Request (Valid Maintainer)
Description: Create an emergency Locate Request
Test_Step_Description:
1. Navigate to the Create Locate Request Page
2. Enter in all Mandatory fields. Ensure that a Maintainer exists for the entered in Subdivision, Mileage From and Mileage To
3. Enter non-mandatory fields : Cell #, Field contact, field contact # and company
4. Click Get Ticket Number
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Ticket gets created and ticket number gets assigned and email gets sent to maintainer

Test_Case_Name: TC07_Create Locate Request - Emergency Request (In-Valid Maintainer)
Description: Create an emergency Locate Request for invalid mainter
Test_Step_Description:
1. Navigate to the Create Locate Request Page
2. Enter in all Mandatory fields. Ensure that a Maintainer does not exists for the entered in Subdivision, Mileage From and Mileage To
3. Enter non-mandatory fields : Cell #, Field contact, field contact # and company
4. Click Get Ticket Number
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Error is thrown - No Maintainer was found for mileage

Test_Case_Name: TC08_Create Locate Request - Non-Emergency Request (Valid Maintainer)
Description: Create an emergency Locate Request
Test_Step_Description:
1. Navigate to the Create Locate Request Page
2. Enter in all Mandatory fields. Ensure that a Maintainer exists for the entered in Subdivision, Mileage From and Mileage To. Ensure date is at least 72 hours past current date and not on a weekend.
3. Enter non-mandatory fields : Cell #, Field contact, field contact # and company
4. Click Get Ticket Number
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Ticket gets created and ticket number gets assigned and email gets sent to maintainer

Test_Case_Name: TC09_Create Locate Request - Non-Emergency Request (In-Valid Maintainer)
Description: Create an emergency Locate Request for invalid mainter
Test_Step_Description:
1. Navigate to the Create Locate Request Page
2. Enter in all Mandatory fields. Ensure that a Maintainer exists for the entered in Subdivision, Mileage From and Mileage To. Ensure date is at least 72 hours past current date and not on a weekend.
3. Enter non-mandatory fields : Cell #, Field contact, field contact # and company
4. Click Get Ticket Number
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Error is thrown - Maintainer is not available for mileage

Description:
Verify that the T94  scan message is processed from AEI server to AEI MF through the Unikix MQ AE.INBOUND.AEL2

Note:
T94 scan format is converted to RBLD format and feed to AEI Unikix
Prerequisites:
1. Mainframe MQ  AE.INBOUND.AEL2 should be triggered ON.
2. User should make sure that the process AEXS0500 is present in Unix directory
Test_Step_Description:
Login to LAPPP0063 and submit T94 scan file in 
the below paths to depart the train from Origin 
station.
'/prod/aei/down/ '
'/prod/aei/eme/down/ '
 
Sample file name: 
AEI0152.01.120105.035660.01.dwn
 
Sample file format attached.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
T94 Files are uploaded successfully in 
LAPPP0063 server in the given paths:
'/prod/aei/down/' and 
'/prod/aei/eme/down/'

Test_Step_Description:
Run the 'execute' script in the below paths:
'/prod/aei/bin' and '/prod/aei/eme/bin'
until the scan files are removed from 
'/prod/aei/down/' and '/acpt/aei/eme/down/' 
directories 


Note:
The files which are uploaded in step 6
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Scan files are successfully removed from the 
'/prod/aei/down/' and '/prod/aei/eme/down/' 
directories after running the 'Execute' script

Test_Step_Description:
Check that the scan file submitted in previous 
step is updated in 
'LAPPP0063/prod/aei/aeiok' directory
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Scan file is successfully updated in 
'/prod/aei/aeiok' directory

Test_Step_Description:
Navigate to the path: 
'LAPPP0063/prod/aei/log/LYYMMDD.LOG' , and 
check that the process AEXS0500 is triggered to 
send the T94 scan information to AEI Unikix
 
Sample log is attached.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The given log should reflect that the AEXS0500 
process is triggered successfully and the T94 
read from AEI server is processed to AEI Unikix.


Log should be updated with appropriate scanner 
id and timestamp

Test_Step_Description:
Login to EME server - LAPPP0014 and go to path 
/prod/eme/bin/eez_12. Check the logs - 
AUDIT.LOG and BAD_DATA.LOG. The scan 
should reach either of these. AUDIT.log will not 
have complete scan but and entry specifying 
scan type will be logged..
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
EME should have received the scan from 
AEI.

Test_Step_Description:
Open Mercator A2A and select the app 'EME 
SADB Scanner'. Put appropriate time in the 
search criteria and look for the scan in the 
results. Note - if the scan was put to 
BAD_DATA.log in EME, it'll not be sent to 
Mercator. In that case, finding the scan in 
BAD_DATA.LOG in the previous step would 
be fine.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Mercator should have the scan if it was 
forwarded by EME.

Test_Step_Description:
Login to LAPPP0063 and submit CP160 scan file 
in the below paths to depart the train from Origin 
station.
'/prod/aei/down/ '
'/prod/aei/eme/down/ '
 
Sample file name: 
AEI0152.01.120105.035660.01.dwn
 
Sample file format attached.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
T94 Files are uploaded successfully in 
LAPPP0063 server in the given paths:
'/prod/aei/down/' and 
'/prod/aei/eme/down/'

Test_Step_Description:
Run the 'execute' script in the below paths:
'/prod/aei/bin' and '/prod/aei/eme/bin'
until the scan files are removed from 
'/prod/aei/down/' and '/acpt/aei/eme/down/' 
directories 


Note:
The files which are uploaded in step 6
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Scan files are successfully removed from the 
'/prod/aei/down/' and '/prod/aei/eme/down/' 
directories after running the 'Execute' script

Test_Step_Description:
Check that the scan file submitted in previous 
step is updated in 
'LAPPP0063/prod/aei/aeiok' directory
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Scan file is successfully updated in 
'/prod/aei/aeiok' directory

Test_Step_Description:
Navigate to the path: 
'LAPPP0063/prod/aei/log/LYYMMDD.LOG' , and 
check that the process AEXS0500 is triggered to 
send the CP160 scan information to AEI Unikix
 
Sample log is attached.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The given log should reflect that the AEXS0500 
process is triggered successfully and the CP160 
read from AEI server is processed to AEI Unikix.


Log should be updated with appropriate scanner 
id and timestamp

Test_Step_Description:
Login to EME server - LAPPP0014 and go to path 
/prod/eme/bin/eez_12. Check the logs - 
AUDIT.LOG and BAD_DATA.LOG. The scan 
should reach either of these. AUDIT.log will not 
have complete scan but and entry specifying 
scan type will be logged..
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
EME should have received the scan from 
AEI.

Test_Step_Description:
Open Mercator A2A and select the app 'EME 
SADB Scanner'. Put appropriate time in the 
search criteria and look for the scan in the 
results. Note - if the scan was put to 
BAD_DATA.log in EME, it'll not be sent to 
Mercator. In that case, finding the scan in 
BAD_DATA.LOG in the previous step would 
be fine.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Mercator should have the scan if it was 
forwarded by EME.

The purpose of this test case is to check the the OASIS applicaiton is able to send  misplacement  summary report by start time and end time to printer

Pre requisite: User is logged in to the OASIS application
Test_Step_Description: click on the "report" menu on the main toolbar
Test_Step_Expected_Result: report menu expands with all the avaialble type of reports

Test_Step_Description: Click on "Misplacement" menu option
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
"Misplacement" report options dialog box opens with the following default settings:-
Drayage co. : <blank>
Driver : <blank>
Start Time: MM:DD:YY(of current day) 00 :00
End Time : MM:DD:YY(of current day)23:59
Report Level: Detailed(preselected)
Output To: Screen(Preselcted)

Test_Step_Description: Select "Printer" from the "Output To" drop down
Test_Step_Expected_Result: A printer selection drop-down appears

Test_Step_Description:
Select the desired printer from the printer selection drop-down
Select "Summary" from the "Report Level" dropdown
Enter a valid Start time
Enter a valid end Time
Click on OK button
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Misplacement Summary report by start and end time is sent to the selected printer

Test_Case_Name: OSS_FNT_CLS_ESYT_001 Train movement from Tyes and valid in OASIS
Test_Step_Description:
1. For Winnipeg(005206), Ingate an unit having waybill # to Vaughan(003409) destination
2. Open Full Track Summary and perform Seed Block for 005206
3. Load the Rail car and Release the railcar having Unit
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Railcar should be released

Test_Step_Description: Locate Equipment 'TTEX 161071'
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Equipment should be displayed

Test_Step_Description:
1. Open 'Profile Lineup' from Train menu and enter Origin and Winnipeg and Destination as Toronto. 
2. Run the Profile.
3. Select 710 Profile symbol and in Add details tab, enter Order time. In Exception tab, Select Reason as 'Crew Availability'. Save the details
4. Click on Find Train button and Enter Train name which was displayed after saving the profile.
5. Select the Train displayed and in the context menu, select Route
6. Change Station Order time and Station Supply time 2 hrs before and save the changes
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Station Order and Supply time should be saved

Test_Step_Description:
1. Select Winnipeg Tyes from File menu. 
2. Select Picker Report from Reports menu. In Location criteria, select RepLoc and enter '05206'. In the Car criteria, enter 'D*'and Run. Check the status of the track and close the report
3. Select Inventory > Track Moves. Enter Track details noted from picker report.
Select Equipment 'TTEX 161071'
4. In Track Moves, enter To Track as WPG track at which the Unit is loaded onto the railcar. Select the Engine which is Empty(E) and Clock on 'Move' button
5. Select menu Equipment > Last Moves to see the last move performed.
6. In Track Moves, select the tracks and press 'Multi move'. Select Train ID. Enter Depart Time. Enter 'To Track' as WIMS. Enter Date and Time and click on 'Move' button
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Track move should be successful

Test_Step_Description: Check Unit Status
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Unit Status should be displayed as Not Available and Load status should be displayed as Enroute to destination

Test_Step_Description:
Select menu Train > Outbound > Outbound. Select Train ID and click on 'Build' button
In Build Outbound Train window, enter Track as WIMS
In Outbound Console, Click on 'Outbound' button
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Outbound should be successful

Test_Step_Description:
In Snapshot scan for a loaded unit, enter Date as Today, Pending as Closed. Click on Find button to see EME message. 
Click on 'Events' button for displayed Unit
Test_Step_Expected_Result: EME message should be displayed

Test_Step_Description: In Find Train Window, update the Station Order Time for Kenora
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Station Order Time should be updated

Test_Step_Description:
Select Train >Inbound > Inbound
In Inbound Train Queue, Select Station as Kenora, ON
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Inbound for Kenora should be displayed

Test_Step_Description: In Find Train Window, update the Station Order Time for Thunder Bay
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Station Order Time should be updated

Test_Step_Description:
Open Tyes for Thunder Bay and select menu Train > Inbound > Inbound. 
Click on Inbound Button. In Fast Inbound window, enter the Inbound Time
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Inbound Time should be updated

Test_Step_Description: Refresh the Unit to display Last Reported at Thunder Bay terminal
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Last Reported time at Thunder Bay should be displayed

Test_Step_Description:
Select menu Train > Outbound > Outbound. Select Train ID and click on 'Build' button. In Build Outbound Train window, enter Train details
In Outbound Console, Click on 'Outbound' button
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Outbound should be successful

Test_Step_Description:
In Snapshot scan for a loaded unit, enter Date as Today, Pending as Closed. Click on Find button to see EME message. 
Click on 'Events' button for displayed Unit
Test_Step_Expected_Result: EME message should be displayed

Test_Step_Description:
Open Tyes for Vaughan. In the Inbound Train Queue, Select Vaughan IMS. Add Approaching Train.  Click on Train Inbound Button.  Click on Inbound Button in Inbound Train Detail screen. 
Click on Inbound Button. In Fast Inbound window, enter the Inbound Time, Track number as per Track present in VGN terminal.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Track number should be displayed as mentioned for VGN

Test_Step_Description: Open the Full Track details provided in Tyes
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Train with the Unit moved from WPG should be displayed on the VGN track

Test_Step_Description: Refresh the Unit to display Status of the Unit
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Unit status should be displayed as "Arrived Inbound Train"

CP Police employee attempts to set the incident 
classification (Event Tag) to one that is not in the 
predetermined list by attempting to enter an 
invalid value into this field.

CP Police employee sets the incident 
classification (Event Tag) to be one of the 
following from a predetermined (configured) 
list:

1. Traffic Warning
2. Traffic Citation
3. Traffic Accident
4. Assault (Critical)
5. Domestic

8. Evading (Critical)

saved on DVR however, video file does not yet 
appear on Evidence Library 3.1

the video file while non-critical Event Tags will 
record a standard version of the video file only.

Test_Case_Name: TC01_Verify Video Management_High Definition Video Footage
Description:
Test goes though and verifies:
 an event type for only a standard version
 an event type for only a HD version
 an event type for both a standard version AND HD version
 then attempts to delete the HD version for an event type containing both a standard version and an HD version
Test_Step_Description:
- Video files exist within Evidence Library 3.1
- Event Types are configured to include:
  1. Event Type that will save video files in HD version
  2. Event Type that will save video files in only standard version
  3. Event Type that will save video files in both HD and standard versions

Step_Name: Step 01. Search Video Files with Event Category for Standard Video

CP Police Supervisor locates and selects video 
files using search by Event Category where 
Event Category can be any one of the following 
(non critical):
 
Traffic Warning
Traffic Citation
Traffic Accident
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
All corresponding video files for the Event 
Category selected are listed.

Test_Step_Description:
For all video files listed in Step 01 verify each has 
only 1 version: a standard video file and NO 
corresponding high definition version of the video 
file.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Video files where Event Category is Traffic 
Warning, Traffic Citation, or Traffic Accident
only have a standard version of the video 
footage and do not have a high definition version.

Step_Name: Step 03. Search Video Files with Event Category for HD Video
Test_Step_Description:
CP Police Supervisor locates and selects video 
files using search by Event Category where 
Event Category can be any one of the following 
(critical category):
 
D.U.I
Assault
Evading
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
All corresponding video files for the Event 
Category selected are listed.

Test_Step_Description: For all video files listed in Step 03 verify each has a HD versions and a standard version of the video file.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Video files where Event Category is  D.U.I, Assault, or Evading only have a high definition version for the Front Camera and a standard 
version for the cabin camera (Aux3).

Step_Name: Step 05. Search Video Files with Event Category for HD and Standard Video

CP Police Supervisor locates and selects video 
files using search by Event Category where 
Event Category is one for which both a standard 
version and an HD version of a video file exists 
for.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
All corresponding video files for the Event 
Category selected are listed.

Step_Name: Step 06. Verify Standard and HD versions

For all video files listed in Step 05 verify each has 
a 2 versions: a standard video file and a 
corresponding high definition version of the video 
file.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Video files  have a high definition and a standard 
version of the video file.

Supervisor selects a high definition version of a 
video file.

Test_Case_Name: TC01_Verify Video Management_High Definition Video Footage
Description:
Test goes though and verifies:
 an event type for only a standard version
 an event type for only a HD version
 an event type for both a standard version AND HD version
 then attempts to delete the HD version for an event type containing both a standard version and an HD version
Test_Step_Description:
- Video files exist within Evidence Library 3.1
- Event Types are configured to include:
  1. Event Type that will save video files in HD version
  2. Event Type that will save video files in only standard version
  3. Event Type that will save video files in both HD and standard versions

Step_Name: Step 01. Search Video Files with Event Category for Standard Video
Test_Step_Description:
CP Police Supervisor locates and selects video 
files using search by Event Category where 
Event Category can be any one of the following 
(non critical):
 
Traffic Warning
Traffic Citation
Traffic Accident
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
All corresponding video files for the Event 
Category selected are listed.

Test_Step_Description:
For all video files listed in Step 01 verify each has 
only 1 version: a standard video file and NO 
corresponding high definition version of the video 
file.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Video files where Event Category is Traffic 
Warning, Traffic Citation, or Traffic Accident
only have a standard version of the video 
footage and do not have a high definition version.

Step_Name: Step 03. Search Video Files with Event Category for HD Video
Test_Step_Description:
CP Police Supervisor locates and selects video 
files using search by Event Category where 
Event Category can be any one of the following 
(critical category):
 
D.U.I
Assault
Evading
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
All corresponding video files for the Event 
Category selected are listed.

Test_Step_Description: For all video files listed in Step 03 verify each has a HD versions and a standard version of the video file.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Video files where Event Category is  D.U.I, Assault, or Evading only have a high definition version for the Front Camera and a standard 
version for the cabin camera (Aux3).

Step_Name: Step 05. Search Video Files with Event Category for HD and Standard Video
Test_Step_Description:
CP Police Supervisor locates and selects video 
files using search by Event Category where 
Event Category is one for which both a standard 
version and an HD version of a video file exists 
for.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
All corresponding video files for the Event 
Category selected are listed.

Step_Name: Step 06. Verify Standard and HD versions
Test_Step_Description:
For all video files listed in Step 05 verify each has 
a 2 versions: a standard video file and a 
corresponding high definition version of the video 
file.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Video files  have a high definition and a standard 
version of the video file.

Test_Step_Description:
From the video files from Step 05 CP Police 
Supervisor selects a high definition version of a 
video file.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: High definition of video footage is selected.

Test_Step_Description:
CP Police Supervisor clicks on "play" to view high 
definition video footage.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Video footage is successfully viewed.

Test_Step_Description:
CP Police Supervisor attempts to delete the high 
definition version of the video footage.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Video footage cannot be deleted.

Description:
Description - To verify if the AEI_T94 message is getting processed in the same way in new acceptance as it is processed in old acceptance.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001  and eez002 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to EDI Application.

Data Requirements - The AEI_T94 message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description: Trigger the AEI_T94 message from AEI Mainframe application.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: AEI_T94 message should get triggered successfully.

Test_Step_Description: Trigger ON the MQ EE.PUB.SUB.03 by using the option 7 - Set trigger control of the MQ util facility.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The MQ should be triggered ON.

Test_Step_Description:
Log into EME Unix application and check the audit log of the program eez001 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez001 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be AEI_T94
After successful processing of AEI_T94 message AEI_T94 message should be created.

Test_Step_Description:
Check the error log of the process eez001.
The location of the error log is /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check if the error record is available for the current message.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The error log should not have any error record for the current message

Test_Step_Description: Trigger ON the MQ EE.SUBSCRIBE.07 by using the option 7 - Set trigger control of the MQ util facility.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The MQ should be triggered ON.

Test_Step_Description:
Log into EME Unix application and check the audit log of the program eez012 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_12
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez012 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be AEI_T94
After successful processing of AEI_T94 message EME_T94 message should be created.

Test_Step_Description:
Check the error log of the process eez012.
The location of the error log is /acpt/eme/bin/eez_12
Check if the error record is available for the current message.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The error log should not have any error record for the current message

Test_Step_Description: Trigger ON the MQ EE.PUB.SUB.04 by using the option 7 - Set trigger control of the MQ util facility.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The MQ should be triggered ON.

Test_Step_Description:
Log into EME Unix application and check the audit log of the program eez001 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez001 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be EME_T94
After successful processing of EME_T94 message EME_T94 message should be created.

Test_Step_Description:
Check the error log of the process eez001.
The location of the error log is /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1

Test_Step_Expected_Result: The error log should not have any error record for the current message

Description:
Description - To validate if  the EME Script EET031 runs sucessfully.

Pre-condition - Failed interchange errors available in DB.

Post Condition -  Updates the table emeapp_failed_msg_hndlng
Test_Step_Description:
Verify if failed data available in the DB using the below query.

  SELECT * FROM emeapp_failed_msg_hndlng hndlng,                                                           
               emeapp_failed_msg        msg,
               emeapp_failed_msg_eqpmt  eqpmt,
               cntl_task_msg_log_rfrnc  rfrnc
         WHERE hndlng.msg_tag_txt = 'TYES_INTRCH'
           AND hndlng.msg_status_cd in ('RETRY', 'FAILED')
           AND hndlng.failed_msg_hndlng_id   = msg.failed_msg_hndlng_id
           AND msg.failed_msg_vrsn_id        = eqpmt.failed_msg_vrsn_id
           AND eqpmt.msg_state_cd            =  'ACTIVE'
           AND hndlng.failed_msg_hndlng_id   = msg.failed_msg_hndlng_id
           AND msg.failed_msg_vrsn_id        = eqpmt.failed_msg_vrsn_id
           AND eqpmt.task_msg_log_id         = rfrnc.task_msg_log_id 
           ORDER BY eqpmt.failed_msg_vrsn_id,    eqpmt.record_create_tms;
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Data should be available in the table.

Test_Step_Description: Navigate to /acpt/eme/scripts and trigger eez031.acpt.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The script should get triggered sucessfully.

Test_Step_Description: verify the audit logs of eez031.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Audit logs should get updated.

Test_Step_Description:
Verify if the data found in step one got processed.
If processed the msg_status_cd should get updated as complete.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The msg_status_cd should get update dto complete.

Test_Step_Description: If the Retry fails atmptd_retry_qty is increased without changing the msg_status_cd .
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The atmptd_retry_qty should get increased.

Test_Step_Description:

Verify if the data found in step one got processed.

Test_Step_Description:
Verify if failed data available in the DB using the below query.

  SELECT * FROM emeapp_failed_msg_hndlng hndlng,                                                           
               emeapp_failed_msg        msg,
               emeapp_failed_msg_eqpmt  eqpmt,
               cntl_task_msg_log_rfrnc  rfrnc
         WHERE hndlng.msg_tag_txt = 'TYES_INTRCH'
           AND hndlng.msg_status_cd in ('RETRY', 'FAILED')
           AND hndlng.failed_msg_hndlng_id   = msg.failed_msg_hndlng_id
           AND msg.failed_msg_vrsn_id        = eqpmt.failed_msg_vrsn_id
           AND eqpmt.msg_state_cd            =  'ACTIVE'
           AND hndlng.failed_msg_hndlng_id   = msg.failed_msg_hndlng_id
           AND msg.failed_msg_vrsn_id        = eqpmt.failed_msg_vrsn_id
           AND eqpmt.task_msg_log_id         = rfrnc.task_msg_log_id 
           ORDER BY eqpmt.failed_msg_vrsn_id,    eqpmt.record_create_tms;
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Data should be available in the table.

Test_Step_Description: Navigate to /acpt/eme/scripts and trigger eez031.acpt.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The script should get triggered sucessfully.

Description:
Test objective:
Verify that the PLACEMENT REPORTS and PIPELINE are generated from MAINFRAME and placed at the following path
/acpt/delta/deltadep/plc/

Pre-requisite:
- Trigger the mainframe job EL@6700 for Pipeline reports
- Trigger the mainframe job EL@6800 for Placement reports

Success Criteria:
- Placement report to be placed at \Delta\Demand\Plc\ UNIX server location

Test Data:
- Trigger mainframe job EL@6700 and EL@6800P
Test_Step_Description:
Trigger the mainframe job EL@6700 and verify that the job completes without any errors

1. Login into MF
2. 3.4
3. EV.DELTA.FTP.JCLLIB
4. F EL@6700P
5. Do a JEM of the JCL
6. Submit the EL@6700P JCL and verify that the job completes successfully

1. cp;15
2. ST

Note: Use the below libraries in the JCL
1) EV.IVS.XCOM.DATA - EV.IVS.XCOM.DATA(EL@6700P)
2) SYS5.XCOM.UNIX.SCRIPT(EL@6700S) - EV.XCOM.UNIX.SCRIPT(EL@6700S)
3) SYS5.XCOM.UNIX.SCRIPT(EL@6700F) - EV.XCOM.UNIX.SCRIPT(EL@6700F)
4) SYS5.XCOM.UNIX.SCRIPT(EL@6700P) - EV.XCOM.UNIX.SCRIPT(EL@6700P)
5) /Prod/delta/deltadep/log/ - > /acpt/delta/deltadep/log/
Test_Step_Expected_Result: EL@6700P job should be completed

Test_Step_Description:
Login into UNIX with valid user credentials and verify that the pipeline report is available at the below UNIX location

/acpt/delta/deltadep/plc/el.pipe.report.csv  
/acpt/delta/deltadep/plc/el.pipe.errors.csv  


Note: MF job EL@6700P is modified to correct UNIX location. Check this in production MF job.

Description:
Description:
To validate if the Actual Outbound 418 (ICHD) Events (Verified data) from TYES is sent to Train SADB via EME and then to WBX.

Pre-Condition:
1. TYES, EME, TSD, WBX should be up and running.
2. All the programs/processes/queues should be up and available in Acceptance.

Post-condition:
1. Actual Outbound 418 data should be successfully sent to Train SADB via EME and the same should be sent across to WBX.

Data Requirements:
1. Valid ICHD events should be created and it should get updated in TSD/WBX after its successful routing and processing.

Stop the queue - 
UT.TRAIN_WBX.OUTBOUND_EDI418.OUTPUT
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The business user should be able to stop the given queue.

Test_Step_Expected_Result: TSD should be updated with the event message details.

Test_Step_Description: Check if the message triggers tsz503 process and updates the TSD.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: TSD should be updated with the event message details.

Description:
Description:
To validate if the Actual Outbound 418 (ICHD) Events (Verified data) from TYES is sent to Train SADB via EME and then to WBX.

Pre-Condition:
1. TYES, EME, TSD, WBX should be up and running.
2. All the programs/processes/queues should be up and available in Acceptance.

Post-condition:
1. Actual Outbound 418 data should be successfully sent to Train SADB via EME and the same should be sent across to WBX.

Data Requirements:
1. Valid ICHD events should be created and it should get updated in TSD/WBX after its successful routing and processing.
Test_Step_Description: Login to Nexus application and create ATP event.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The business user should be able to create ATP event.

Test_Step_Description: Login to TYES and build the train. Create ICHD events.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The business user should be able to build a train and create ICHD events.

Test_Step_Description:
Stop the queue - 
UT.TRAIN_WBX.OUTBOUND_EDI418.OUTPUT
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The business user should be able to stop the given queue.

Test_Step_Description: Check if the ICHD events data in TYES is passed onto EME and check if this event message is put onto UT.TYES_TRAIN.OUTBOUND_EDI418.INPUT queue.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The message should be available on the UT.TYES_TRAIN.OUTBOUND_EDI418.INPUT queue.

Test_Step_Description: Check if the message triggers tsz503 process and updates the TSD.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: TSD should be updated with the event message details.

Test_Step_Description: Check if the message triggers tsz503 process and updates the TSD.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: TSD should be updated with the event message details.

Test_Step_Description: Check if the message with Events 418 (Final) is placed on the queue UT.TRAIN_WBX.OUTBOUND_EDI418.OUTPUT, routed to WBX.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The message containing the Events 418 (Final) should be available on the UT.TRAIN_WBX.OUTBOUND_EDI418.OUTPUT queue.

Test_Step_Description: Start the queue - UT.TRAIN_WBX.OUTBOUND_EDI418.OUTPUT and check with WBX if data is received on their end.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The given queue should get started and the Events 418 (Final) data should be received on WBX side.

Description: This test case is to verify the demand management tool after the DB server is upgraded for the same.
Test_Step_Description:
Verify following steps are performed for DMT and they are working.


PO Team (Sakhti) confirmed that PI/PO on QA2 is pointing to ORAS432 using new oracle driver 
Customer  Station team retrieved / fetched the Master Train record 



e.g. Customer  Station team retrieved / fetched the Master Train record between Vaughan and Calgary from newer database of ORAS432







Customer  Station team updated  Non Essential Capacity of the Train 101 for Sunday  to 1234 from 1500. 
Customer  Station team verified that the  Non Essential Capacity of the Train 101 for Sunday updated  to 1234 from 1500in the newer Database ORAS432 and no changes were made / updated in previous ORAS132 (older database).
By confirming Read/Write/Update operations are working properly, its confirmed that db drivers are working properly after connecting to new Database.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Following steps work fine without issues.


PO Team (Sakhti) confirmed that PI/PO on QA2 is pointing to ORAS432 using new oracle driver 
Customer  Station team retrieved / fetched the Master Train record 



e.g. Customer  Station team retrieved / fetched the Master Train record between Vaughan and Calgary from newer database of ORAS432







Customer  Station team updated  Non Essential Capacity of the Train 101 for Sunday  to 1234 from 1500. 
Customer  Station team verified that the  Non Essential Capacity of the Train 101 for Sunday updated  to 1234 from 1500in the newer Database ORAS432 and no changes were made / updated in previous ORAS132 (older database).
By confirming Read/Write/Update operations are working properly, its confirmed that db drivers are working properly after connecting to new Database.

Test_Case_Name: Verify Placement Events in Yard Logistics
Description:
Yard Logistics obtains the events from SAP EM application to display the appropriate status of the railcar event for 
the users at the auto compounds.

All railcars that are reported as placed on the industry tracks at the auto compounds are displayed on the handheld 
devices in the placed status.
Test_Step_Description:
Point tha SAP PO queues to the landscape being tested.

Queue (XI.EME.EQUIP_EVENT.RECEIVE.04) should be pointed to either the QA1 landscape or QA2 landscape.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Queue pointed to the landscape being tested

Test_Step_Description:
Identify railcars that exist in all the following applications for the landscape being tested in.
1. TYES
2. SADB EMIS
3. SAP PM
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Successfully identified railcars that exist in all the regions

Test_Step_Description:
Login to TYES, 
1. Select the railcar that are NOT in placed status
2. If the railcars are NOT already on the auto compounds industry tracks, force move these railcars to these tracks 
by navigating to Supervisor ==> Add Inventory.
3. After closing the Add Inventory screen, Navigate toTrain ==> Release Switch, select the track, OCS, railcar and 
right click to place the railcar.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Successfully placed railcar in TYES

Test_Step_Description: Verify placement event in SADB EME
Test_Step_Expected_Result: placement event successfully verified in SADB EME

Test_Step_Description:
Verify placement event in Yard Logistics handheld device
1. Logon to SAP Yard Logistics using a handheld device or Fiori
2. Navigate to the auto compound the railcar was placed at
3. Select the Spot Railcar function
4. Verify railcar in Placede status
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Successfully verified the placement status of the railcar in SAP Yard Logistics mobile handheld device.

Test_Case_Name: BPLA_FVTC_0440_TS-239 Verify Placement variance tracking - PACT Segment
Description:
Verify the functionality associated with changes to the Customer RAD time of the Destination Anchor.
Refer to JIRA item TS-239 Destination Placement variance tracking (PACT segment)
Test_Step_Description:
This test requires 
1. a user that has the permission required to access the NexTrain application.
2. necessary NexTrain lineup group is created with Origin and Destination anchor selected and group saved.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Pre-condition is satisfied.

Test_Step_Description: Verify that the Dest Place Time is defaulted automatically as AOMTS + Destination Runtime of the destination archor selected.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Dest Place Time displayed as described.

Test_Step_Description: Right click the group entry in the NexTrain Lineup screen and select the NexTrain Variances option from the Context menu that opens.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The NexTrain Variance screen open without error and is available for use in this test.

Step_Name: 3. Verify no PACT Variance Type Entry
Test_Step_Description: Verify that there is a record with Variance Type PACT in the variances screen with Variance Amt 00:00 OT
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The specified record exist with Variance Amt 00:00 OT

Test_Step_Description:
Update (if possible directly on screen or by different means) AOMTS value of the destination anchor train in route screen and save.
Verify that the Dest Place Time is re-calculated and displayed on-screen automatically as current AOMTS + Destination Runtime
Test_Step_Expected_Result: AOMTS value is saved and Dest Place Time re-calculated as defined.

Test_Step_Description:
Update (if possible directly on screen or by different means) Run Time value of the destination anchor train and save.
Verify that the Dest Place Time is re-calculated and displayed on-screen automatically as AOMTS + new Destination Runtime, only when DOMTS of Origin Anchor, Origin Anchor train or ORT changes
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Run Time value is saved and Dest Place Time re-calculated as defined.

Test_Step_Description: Overide default Dest Place time as default Dest Place time+ 5 hours and save the change.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The overide value Dest Place time is saved and highlighted in yellow.

Test_Step_Description: Verify that the PACT variance record is created in  NexTrain Variances with variance of 5 hour LT.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: PACT record is created with all other details correctly populated including Variance Amt 5 hr LT.

Test_Step_Description:
Verify that alert is also created for PACT variance in the tasklist.
Note: For alert to display, the variance amount should be greater than the Threshold defined in the Exception Reporting Rule Editor for PACT.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Alert is displayed on task list as described.

Test_Step_Description: Overide AOMTS of destination anchor as current AOMTS - 1 hours in the route screen and save the change.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The overide value AOMTS is saved.

Test_Step_Description: Verify that the PACT variance record is updated in  NexTrain Variances with variance of 6 hour LT.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: PACT record is updated with all other details correctly populated including Variance Amt 6 hr LT.

Step_Name: 11. Verify Previous Variance Proportional Adjustment Alert
Test_Step_Description:
Verify that the PACT variance  is re-calculated as (AOMTS + Destination Runtime)-Dest Place Time
For a variance that is to be alerted based on the Variance Threshold defined in the Exception Reporting Rule Editor, verify that there is an alert in Nexus task list
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Variance is re-calculated and alerted as specified

Test_Step_Description:
Verify that alert is still displayed for PACT variance in the tasklist.
Note: For alert to display, the variance amount should be greater than the Threshold defined in the Exception Reporting Rule Editor for PACT.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Alert is displayed on task list as described.

Test_Step_Description:
Overide AOMTS of destination anchor again as current AOMTS + 8 hours and save the change.
Verify that the Dest Place Time is re-set automatically as AOMTS + Destination Runtime because AOMTS + Destination Runtime exceeds a manually entered Dest Place Time.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The overide value AOMTS is saved and Dest Place Time is set to default value.

Test_Step_Description: Verify that the PACT variance record is expired in  NexTrain Variances as there is no variance currently. Observe if anything inapproprite.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Variance screen display modified as expected.

Test_Step_Description: Verify that PACT alert is removed in the tasklist.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Alert is removed in task list as described.

Test_Step_Description:
Overide AOMTS of destination anchor again as current AOMTS - 2 hours and save the change.
Verify that the Dest Place Time is re-set automatically as AOMTS + Destination Runtime because the current Dest Place Time is not manual overide.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The overide value AOMTS is saved and Dest Place Time is set to default value.

Test_Step_Description: Verify that there is No PACT variance record in  NexTrain Variances screen.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Variance screen display as expected.

Test_Step_Description: Verify that there is no PACT alert is in the tasklist.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: No Alert is displayed in task list as described.

Test_Step_Description: Try to acualize Dest Place time before actualizing the AOMTS on the Destination Anchor Train
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
System should not allow the user to acualize Dest Place 
time.

Step_Name: 20. Actualize AOMTS and then Dest Place time
Test_Step_Description:
Acualize  the AOMTS on the Destination Anchor Train and then Dest Place time and save.
Note: The system should not allow the Actual Dest Place time earlier than AOMTS.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The actualization of times get saved and system behaves as described.

Test_Step_Description: Close all windows opened during this test.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: All windows opened during this test are closed.

Description:
Subdivision TGBO Number Increments

Sub TGBO

Verify: Subdivision TGBO number increments(3). Check this by view subdivision.

Note - again , takes a few minutes

Verify:  GBO just created is present in each case.
Subdivision TGBO (4) (5) (6)

Test_Step_Description: Create 2 more GBO (5, 6) and print the subdivision TGBO after each one

Verify:  Each GBO is present and order is correct.
Sub TGBO (7) (8)

Test_Step_Description: Supply Train 4 in the opposite direction and Acknowledge another train.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Verify:  Status has changed from <LS> to (AK)

Test_Step_Description: Release Train 2's TGBO but don't delete the supply

Test_Step_Description: From TGBO, compare Train 2 - just released with Subdivision TGBO (5)
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Verify:  protection list generated showing 3 GBO's (4, 5, 6)

Test_Step_Description: Protect GBO (4, 6) with "Thru Limits" Deliver GBO (5) on the protection to the train and select <Complete>

Description:

1. Cost
2. Distance (Canada & US)
3. Penalty Distance
4. Repeated Miles in US
5. New Miles( for the route)
6. Closest better path in US only
7. Reverse Closest path in US
8. Circuitousness("Self %" on the prototype) for entire route

Test_Step_Expected_Result: The Canadian distance, US distand and total distance is displayed for each of the alternate routes generated

Test_Step_Expected_Result: The Reserve Closest path in US is displayed for each of the alternate routes generated

The circuitousness(Self%)  is 
displayed for each of the alternate routes generated

10.	Send pass on same day in step 6 or 7

Test_Step_Description: Train stops at signal and waits for signal to clear.
Train does not stop for stop requested signal. This is okay.
Train does stop for signal in time.
If stick move over non-lined OS
Test_Step_Expected_Result: confirm count does not increment

Test_Step_Description: If stick move over lined OS
Test_Step_Expected_Result: confirm count does increment

Test_Step_Description: Confirm count will increment is signal is CR, CL or SR/CL
Confirm count is shown for all non-OS tracks in route. Check case where two non-OS tracks (eg: T01 and T01).
Confirm count is not shown for all OS tracks in route. Check case where two OS tracks (eg: T02 and T04).
For basic increment, approach need not be occupied

Test_Case_Name: 3.14.1 Count Increment (Create Occupancy -- Basic Count Increment)
Test_Step_Description: If stick move over non-lined OS
Test_Step_Expected_Result: confirm occupancy not created

Test_Step_Description: If stick move over lined OS
Test_Step_Expected_Result: confirm occupancy created

Test_Step_Description: Confirm occupancy created if is signal is CR, CL or SR/CL
Confirm occupancy created even if other non-OS tracks on the route. (Portage or Walkerville)
Only OS is needed, confirm approach need not be down in order to create occupancy

Test_Case_Name: 3.14.2 Count Increment (Create Occupancy -- Guard OS Tracks)
Test_Step_Description: If two or more OS tracks, occupancy is only created for occupancy of guarded OS track. Count does not increment when other OS is occupied. (Virden)
If other OS is occupied first then occupancy is still created when guarded gets occupied. (Virden)
If two or more OS tracks, count is only incremented for event on guarded OS. Count does not increment when other OS is occupied.
If other OS is occupied first then count still increments when guarded gets occupied.

Test_Case_Name: 3.13.3 Count Decrement (Normal Forward Move, Basic Forward Clear)
Test_Step_Description:
When a lined OS track reports unoccupied, all tracks to the rear are decremented. NOTE: to check this, a track must remain occupied in the block to the rear.
NOTE: to qualify as forward move, the track ahead of the OS must be occupied
Confirm decrement does not occur if OS is not lined.

Test decrement to rear under 3 occupancy scenario: 
Closest track remains down (slow pick scenario) or, 
Far approach remains down or,
Adjoining OS remains down.

Test_Case_Name: 3.14.3 Count Decrement (Remove Occupancy -- Basic Forward Clear)
Test_Step_Description: When OS reports unoccupied for train leaving siding confirm occupancy is removed. NOTE: track ahead must be occupied else considered a head room move.
Confirm occupancy is not removed if OS is not lined.

Test_Case_Name: 3.14.4 Count Decrement (Remove Occupancy -- Guard OS Tracks)
Test_Step_Description: If two or more OS tracks, occupancy is only removed for unoccupancy of guarded OS.
In multi OS scenario where two trains are in siding, confirm we do not end up removing both occupancies. That is T02 YA and then T04YA (Virden)

Test_Case_Name: 3.13.4 Count Decrement (Normal Forward Move, Guard OS Tracks)
Test_Step_Description: If two or more OS tracks, count is only decremented for event on guarded OS.

In multi OS scenario:
Confirm that occupancy of second OS is enough to confirm forward move.
Confirm that occupancy of first non-OS is enough to confirm forward move.

When a lined OS track reports unoccupied, if track ahead is not down then train is backing up, in this case all tracks ahead are decremented and tracks to the rear are not affected. NOTE: To test this, have adjoining approach ahead occupied in order to hold a count.
Confirm that backup clearing works in multi-OS scenario.

Description: ABC/F test requirement pop up
Test_Step_Description:
1.	Find ENG on pending requirement screen with ABC test set to NA
2.	Send ABC test less than 1 year as fail
3.	Review pending requirements for fail
4.	Send ABC test for the same day as a pass
5.	Review pending requirements for a Pass
6.	On the day after that was used in step 4 Send ABC test type 1234.11a, 1234.11b, 1234.11c as a pass
7.	On the day used in step 6 send fail for all three test
8.	Review pending requirement ABC test pop up
9.	Send fail on same day in step 6 or 7
10.	Send pass on same day in step 6 or 7
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Employee should have a fail and a pass on the days used in step 2 and 4.  Employee should have 3 passes and 3 fails on the day used in step 6 and 7

Test_Step_Description:

9.	Send fail on same day in step 6 or 7
10.	Send pass on same day in step 6 or 7
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Employee should have a fail and a pass on the days used in step 2 and 4.  Employee should have 3 passes and 3 fails on the day used in step 6 and 7

Test_Step_Description:

Test_Step_Expected_Result: Employee should have a fail and a pass on the days used in step 2 and 4.  Employee should have a pass and a fail on the day used in step 6 and 7

Description: This test case is to verify the functionality of edit of movement instructions.
Test_Step_Description: Launch EIC. Open a TOP.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: EIC is displayed.

Test_Step_Description:
Issue or select an existing  Movement Instructions (work).

Edit the Clear location and Clear time fields.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Clear location and Clear time fields are not editable and also Clear option is not available for work instruction.

Test_Step_Description:
Pre-requisite - There is an existing Movement Instructions with proceed instructions.

Edit the Clear location and Clear time fields.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Clear location can be edited and Clear time field is non-editable.

Test_Step_Description: Verify that clear of location and time are populated with the last values saved.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Clear of location and time are populated with the last values saved.

Test_Step_Description:
Verify that clear of location can be selected from a list of dispatchable points or entered as a valid whole mile.
- Select Mile... option and enter a Mile that is outside the MI limits. Select Clear
- Select Mile... opiton and enter a valid mile within the MI limits. Select Clear
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Clear of location can be selected from a list of dispatchable points or entered as a valid whole mile.
List of points includes only ones that are within the limits ot the MI.
Mile option is at the last one in the list.
Prompt if invalid mile:
"Invalid milepost value.
Must be between <low limit mile> and <high limit mile>" (OK)

Test_Step_Description:
Do not change the location and click on the Clear button (on a new MI or one that hasn't been previously cleared)
Select Close after acknowledging the prompt.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
A prompt "No clear location selected is displayed with Ok button.
Close can be selected and closes the TOP

Test_Step_Description: Selecty a clear location and click on the Clear button.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The clear time is auto generated and not editable. It is in hhmm format.

Test_Step_Description: Repeat a Clear process with a different location.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Clear is allowed and newly selected location overwrites the previous one. 
Clear Time is generated again and overwrites the previous one.

Description:
Description:
To validate if the purge job DMRG_ PURGE.DMRG_PURGE_MAIN purges -  All DMRG log statements which are older than 10 days

Pre-Condition:
1. Logs that should be purged by the purge job should exist in the database.

Post-condition:
1. Statement logs and other mentioned logs should be purged after the execution of the purge job.

Data Requirements:
1. Statement logs older than 10 days and other mentioned logs older than 550 days should pre- exist in the database.
Test_Step_Description:
Run the demurrage batch job dmrg_purge.sh
The path for the executable script is -
/acpt/dmrg/script
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Purge batch job should run successfully.

Description: Verify the performance of the CPR Display Activity Summary page.
Test_Step_Description: Selecting the Closed Cycles link.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Capture the time taken for the Statement Summary and Activity Summary pane to change to the following options:
A. Statement Summary
1. Customer
2. Station Name
3. Statement Date
4. Version 
5. Status
6. Activity
B. Activity Summary
1. Calculation Method
2. Denurrage Date
3. Sumary Credit Release Date
4. Chargeable Demurrage Days
5. Rate
6. Subtotal (Rate * Chargeable Demurrage Days)
7. Other Charges
8. Summary Charge Relief
9. Total Charges
If the Statement Amount is 0, then the summary information under the Activity Summary will changed as follows:
1. Calculation Method
2. Rate
3. Demurrage Amount
4. Other Charges
5. Monetary Relief
6. Subtotal
7. Summary Charge Relief
8. Total Charges

A. Statement Summary
1. Customer
2. Station Name
3. Statement Date
4. Version 
5. Status
6. Activity
B. Activity Summary
1. Calculation Method
2. Denurrage Days
If the Statement Amount is 0, then the summary information under the Activity Summary will changed as follows:
1. Calculation Method
2. Rate

Description: Verify the performance of the CPR Display Activity Summary page.
Test_Step_Description: Selecting the Empty IO or Load IO link.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The Empty IO link will appear if the Statement status is showing LOCKED or showing OPEN but the amount is 0.
The Load IO link appears if the Statement status is showing OPEN with a sum amount.
Capture the time taken for the Statement Summary and Activity Summary pane to change to the following options in case of Empty IO with amount and Load IO:
A. Statement Summary
1. Customer
2. Station Name
3. Statement Date
4. Version 
5. Status
6. Activity
B. Activity Summary
1. Calculation Method
2. Denurrage Days
In case of Empty IO with the Statement Amount as 0, then the summary information under the Activity Summary will changed as follows:
1. Calculation Method
2. Rate

Description:
Description - To verify if the CIM_SHOPPINGmessage is getting processed in the same way in new acceptance as it is processed in old acceptance.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001and eez002 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1)  Message should be passed to R1 application.

Data Requirements - The CIM_SHOPPING message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description: Trigger theCIM_SHOPPING message from CIM application.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: CIM_SHOPPING message should get triggered successfully.

Test_Step_Description: Trigger ON the MQ EE.PUB.SUB.01 by using the option 7 - Set trigger control of the MQ util facility.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The MQ should be triggered ON.

Test_Step_Description:
Log into EME Unix application and check the audit log of the program eez001 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez001 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be CIM_SHOPPING
After successful processing of CIM_SHOPPING message CIM_SHOPPING message should be created.

Test_Step_Description:
Check the error log of the process eez001.
The location of the error log is /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check if the error record is available for the current message.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The error log should not have any error record for the current message

Test_Step_Description: Trigger ON the MQ EE.SUBSCRIBE.01 by using the option 7 - Set trigger control of the MQ util facility.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The MQ should be triggered ON.

Test_Step_Description:
Check the audit log of the program eez002 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_2
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez002 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be CIM_SHOPPING
After successful processing of CIM_SHOPPING message BADOR message should be created.

Test_Step_Description:
Check the error log of the process eez002.
The location of the error log is /acpt/eme/bin/eez_2
Check if the error record is available for the current message.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The error log should not have any error record for the current message

Test_Step_Expected_Result: The Message should get updated in the Table.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001, eez015 and eez017 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to CAR HISTORY Application.

Data Requirements - The TYES_TRKMV_UP2 message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description: Trigger the TYES_TRKMV_UP2 message from TYES application.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: TYES_TRKMV_UP2 message should get triggered successfully.

Test_Step_Description: Trigger ON the MQ EE.PUB.SUB.05 by using the option 7 - Set trigger control of the MQ util facility.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The MQ should be triggered ON.

Test_Step_Description:
Log into EME Unix application and check the audit log of the program eez001 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez001 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be TYES_TRKMV_UP2
After successful processing of TYES_TRKMV_UP2 message TYES_TRKMV_UP2 message should be created.

Test_Step_Description:
Check the error log of the process eez001.
The location of the error log is /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check if the error record is available for the current message.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The error log should not have any error record for the current message

Test_Step_Description: Trigger ON the MQ EE.SUBSCRIBE.14 by using the option 7 - Set trigger control of the MQ util facility.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The MQ should be triggered ON.

The message should be successfully processed by the eez015 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to TSD Application.

Data Requirements - The TYES_DFLC message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description: Trigger the TYES_DFLC message from TYES application.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: TYES_DFLC message should get triggered successfully.

Test_Step_Description: Trigger ON the MQ EE.PUB.SUB.07 by using the option 7 - Set trigger control of the MQ util facility.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The MQ should be triggered ON.

Test_Step_Description:
Log into EME Unix application and check the audit log of the program eez001 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez001 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be TYES_DFLC
After successful processing of TYES_DFLC message TYES_DFLC message should be created.

Test_Step_Description:
Check the error log of the process eez001.
The location of the error log is /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check if the error record is available for the current message.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The error log should not have any error record for the current message

Test_Step_Description: Trigger ON the MQ EE.SUBSCRIBE.10 by using the option 7 - Set trigger control of the MQ util facility.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001, eez002 and eez013 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to CUSTOMS Application.

Data Requirements - The TRAIN II (Train 73) message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description:
Log into EME Unix application and check the audit log of the program eez001 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez001 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be EME_PUB_TRNII
After successful processing of EME_PUB_TRNII message EME_PUB_TRNII message should be created.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001, eez002, and eez009 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to Delta Mainframe Application.

Data Requirements - The BADOR (Heavy Load) message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description:
Log into EME Unix application and check the audit log of the program eez009 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_09
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez009 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be EME_PUB_BO
After successful processing of EME_PUB_BO message EME_PUB_DELTA (TOHBADORDR) message should be created.

Test_Step_Description:

Test_Step_Expected_Result: The error log should not have any error record for the current message

Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez001 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be BADOR
After successful processing of BADOR message, BADOR message should be created.

Description:
Description - To verify if the BADOR message is getting processed in the same way in new acceptance as it is processed in old acceptance.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001 and eez002 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to EDI Application.

Data Requirements - The BADOR message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description:
Check the error log of the process eez001.
The location of the error log is /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check if the error record is available for the current message.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The error log should not have any error record for the current message

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001, eez002 and eez017 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to CAR HISTORY Application.

Data Requirements - The TRAIN message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description:
Check the error log of the process eez017.
The location of the error log is /acpt/eme/bin/eez_17
Check if the error record is available for the current message.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The error log should not have any error record for the current message

Description:
Description - To verify if the TRAIN message is getting processed in the same way in new acceptance as it is processed in old acceptance.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001, eez002 and eez017 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to CAR HISTORY Application.

Data Requirements - The TRAIN message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description:
Log into EME Unix application and check the audit log of the program eez001 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez001 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be TRAIN
After successful processing of TRAIN message, TRAIN message should be created.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001 and eez002 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to VISTA MF.

Data Requirements - The TRAIN message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description:
Log into  Vista mainframe and check if the Message has reached the  MQ ITMS.MOVE_EVENT.ROUTING.
Check the following parameters in the MQ.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach Vista MF application and value of the parameters in MQ should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be EME_PUB_TRAIN2

Description:
Description - To verify if the TRAIN message is getting processed in the same way in new acceptance as it is processed in old acceptance.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001, eez002, eez002 and eez013 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should get processed and passed to TSD application.

Data Requirements - The TRAIN message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description: Trigger the TRAIN message from TRAIN application.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: TRAIN message should get triggered successfully.

Description:
Description - To verify if the TRAIN message is getting processed in the same way in new acceptance as it is processed in old acceptance.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001, eez002, eez002 and eez013 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should get processed and passed to TSD application.

Data Requirements - The TRAIN message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description: Trigger ON the MQ EE.PUB.SUB.01 by using the option 7 - Set trigger control of the MQ util facility.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The MQ should be triggered ON.

Description:
Description - To verify if the TRAIN message is getting processed in the same way in new acceptance as it is processed in old acceptance.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001, eez002, eez002 and eez013 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should get processed and passed to TSD application.

Data Requirements - The TRAIN message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description:
Log into EME Unix application and check the audit log of the program eez001 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez001 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be TRAIN
After successful processing of TRAIN message, TRAIN message should be created.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001 and eez009 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to DELTA UNIX Application.

Data Requirements - The TRAIN message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description:
Log into EME Unix application and check the audit log of the program eez001 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez001 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be EME_PUB_TRAIN2
After successful processing of EME_PUB_TRAIN2 message EME_PUB_TRAIN2 message should be created.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001 and eez002 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to VISTA MF.

Data Requirements - The TRAIN message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description: Trigger ON the MQ EE.PUB.SUB.01 by using the option 7 - Set trigger control of the MQ util facility.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The MQ should be triggered ON.

Description:
Description - To verify if the TRAIN message is getting processed in the same way in new acceptance as it is processed in old acceptance.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001 and eez002 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to VISTA MF.

Data Requirements - The TRAIN message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description:
Log into EME Unix application and check the audit log of the program eez001 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez001 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be TRAIN
After successful processing of TRAIN message, TRAIN message should be created.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001 and eez002 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to TRIEX application.

Data Requirements - The TRAIN message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description: Trigger ON the MQ EE.SUBSCRIBE.02 by using the option 7 - Set trigger control of the MQ util facility.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The MQ should be triggered ON.

Description:
Description - To verify if the TRAIN message is getting processed in the same way in new acceptance as it is processed in old acceptance.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001 and eez002 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to TRIEX application.

Data Requirements - The TRAIN message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description:
Check the audit log of the program eez002 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_2
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez002 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be TRAIN
After successful processing of TRAIN message EME_PUB_TRAIN5 message should be created.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to TMS application.

Data Requirements - The CNVYNG_WYBL_2 message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description:
Log into EME Unix application and check the audit log of the program eez001 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez001 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be CSD_CSTMS_REQ
After successful processing of CSD_CSTMS_REQ message, CSD_CSTMS_REQ message should be created.

Description:
Description - To validate if retry daemon eez035 is trying to resend EME movements messages again to TSD.
To test this scenario keep this daemon ON and check the audit log of this process in case the EME movement message is failed. 

Pre-condition - daemon process eez035 should be running in the background.

Post Condition - EME movement messages should be sent to TSD.

Data Requirements - NA
Test_Step_Description: Trigger the Train movement message TYES ARIL, TYES PASSING or TYES DEPART from TYES with the invalid data so that the message should get failed in EME.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Train movement message should be failed in the EME.

Description:
Description - To validate if retry daemon eez035 is trying to resend EME movements messages again to TSD.
To test this scenario keep this daemon ON and check the audit log of this process in case the EME movement message is failed. 

Pre-condition - daemon process eez035 should be running in the background.

Post Condition - EME movement messages should be sent to TSD.

Data Requirements - NA
Test_Step_Description:
Check the message in EME failed tables.
SELECT * FROM emeapp_failed_msg_hndlng 
hndlng, 
emeapp_failed_msg msg,
emeapp_failed_msg_eqpmt eqpmt,
cntl_task_msg_log_rfrnc rfrnc
WHERE hndlng.msg_tag_txt in 
('YARDS','EME_PUB_TRAIN1','EME_PUB_TRAIN2','EME_PUB_TRAIN3','EME_ARIL','TYES_DMRG','TYES_INTRCH','UACGC996RELEAS') -- 
AND hndlng.msg_status_cd in ('FAILED')
AND hndlng.failed_msg_hndlng_id = 
msg.failed_msg_hndlng_id
AND msg.failed_msg_vrsn_id = 
eqpmt.failed_msg_vrsn_id
AND eqpmt.msg_state_cd = 'ACTIVE'
AND hndlng.failed_msg_hndlng_id = 
msg.failed_msg_hndlng_id
AND msg.failed_msg_vrsn_id = 
eqpmt.failed_msg_vrsn_id
AND eqpmt.task_msg_log_id = 
rfrnc.task_msg_log_id 
ORDER BY eqpmt.failed_msg_vrsn_id, 
eqpmt.record_create_tms;
Test_Step_Expected_Result: EME message failed table should have the record for the message.

Description:
Description - To validate if EME successfully receive and processes the CSTMS_CSD_01 message triggered by CUSTOMS. EME should route this message to CSD for further processing.
CSD should process CSTMS_CSD_01 and generate CSD_EQPMT_ID message. CSD_EQPMT_ID message should be successfully received by the EME.
EME should again route this message to CSD for further processing.
CSD should process CSD_EQPMT_ID and generate CSD_PUB_WYBL message.
CSD_PUB_WYBL message should be successfully received by EME and forwarded to SHPMNT A application.

Test_Case_Name: TC_EME_TSD_Actuals from MTP to TSD via EME
Description:
Description - To verify if the TSD (ACTUALS) message is getting processed in the same way in new acceptance as it is processed in old acceptance.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001 should be triggered ON at EME and tsz001 at TSD.

Post-condition - 1) Message should get processed and passed to TSD application.

Data Requirements - The TSD (ACTUALS) message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description: Trigger the TSD (ACTUALS) message from MTP application.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: TSD (ACTUALS) message should get triggered successfully.

Test_Case_Name: TC_EME_TSD_Actuals from MTP to TSD via EME
Description:
Description - To verify if the TSD (ACTUALS) message is getting processed in the same way in new acceptance as it is processed in old acceptance.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001 should be triggered ON at EME and tsz001 at TSD.

Post-condition - 1) Message should get processed and passed to TSD application.

Data Requirements - The TSD (ACTUALS) message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description: Trigger ON the MQ EE.PUB.SUB.01 by using the option 7 - Set trigger control of the MQ util facility.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The MQ should be triggered ON.

Test_Case_Name: TC_EME_TSD_Actuals from MTP to TSD via EME
Description:
Description - To verify if the TSD (ACTUALS) message is getting processed in the same way in new acceptance as it is processed in old acceptance.

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001 should be triggered ON at EME and tsz001 at TSD.

Post-condition - 1) Message should get processed and passed to TSD application.

Data Requirements - The TSD (ACTUALS) message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description:
Log into EME Unix application and check the audit log of the program eez001 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_1
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez001 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be TSD (ACTUALS)
After successful processing of TSD (ACTUALS) message TSD (ACTUALS) message should be created.

Description:
Description:

2. All the programs/processes/queues should be up and available in Acceptance.

Post-condition:
1. Actual Outbound 418 data should be successfully sent to Train SADB via EME and the same should be sent across to WBX.

Data Requirements:
1. Valid ICHD events should be created and it should get updated in TSD/WBX after its successful routing and processing.
Test_Step_Description: Check if the message triggers tsz503 process and updates the TSD.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: TSD should be updated with the event message details.

Test_Step_Description:
define range to be purged



Set control_value 
on table emeapp_purge_control



This determines the number of days 
since last purge.



select sysdate-4971 from dual
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
records are evaluated for:
- falling within the specified date 
range
- equipment number
- mark code
- event id
(the four criteria are grouped) 



if these values exist on the 
shpmt_trip_plan_event_msg table, they will not 
be selected for delete

Test_Step_Description:
Select the rows that will be deleted 
and export the result     






Select all ROWIDs within this date range
SELECT /*+ 
INDEX(t1, eqpmv_rfeqp_mvmnt_event_ix04) */
           
t1.ROWID a, event_id, mark_cd, eqpun_nbr
      FROM eqpmv_rfeqp_mvmnt_event t1
     WHERE 
t1.record_update_tms BETWEEN to_date('1999022213:12:43','yyyymmddhh24:mi:ss')
    AND to_date('1999022221:12:43','yyyymmddhh24:mi:ss')
       AND NOT EXISTS (
            SELECT /*+ 
INDEX(t2, eqpmv_last_lctn_prcs_pk) */
                 
t2.mark_cd, t2.eqpun_nbr
              FROM eqpmv_last_lctn_prcs t2
             WHERE t2.mark_cd             = t1.mark_cd
              AND t2.eqpun_nbr           = t1.eqpun_nbr
               --Infosys Changes for ASR3295655 
Starts: 05-Apr-2011
               /*Last movement event ID of 
the eqpmv_last_lctn_prcs is compared
              
with the event ID of eqpmv_rfeqp_mvmnt_event table to check whether 
               
the event details are referenced in LLP table or not.*/               
               AND (t2.last_mvmnt_event_id     = t1.event_id
               --Infosys Changes for ASR3295655 
Ends: 05-Apr-2011
                OR t2.intrch_dlvry_event_id    = t1.event_id
                OR t2.intrch_rcpt_event_id     = t1.event_id
                OR t2.bad_order_event_id       = t1.event_id
                OR t2.status_event_id          = t1.event_id
                OR t2.dmrg_event_id            = t1.event_id
                OR t2.mvmnt_event_id           = t1.event_id
                OR t2.aei_event_id             = t1.event_id
                OR t2.track_mvmnt_event_id     = t1.event_id
                OR t2.trip_end_event_id        = t1.event_id
                OR t2.clsfct_event_id          = t1.event_id)) 
        AND NOT EXISTS (
            SELECT /*+ 
INDEX(t3,shpmt_trppln_event_msg_ix01) */
                    
t3.event_id,
                   
t3.mark_cd,
                   
t3.eqpun_nbr
                 FROM shpmt_trip_plan_event_msg t3
             WHERE t3.event_id  = t1.event_id
               AND t3.mark_cd   = t1.mark_cd
               AND t3.eqpun_nbr = t1.eqpun_nbr);

Test_Case_Name: UR8-TC8-Add a junction interchange and settlement with atleast one CP station via EDI
Description: The test verifies that an IRF message with interchange details is published to SAP when an EDI to add a new interchange or a settlement on an interchange that has atleast one stations (origin or destination) as a CPRS station, is processed. Also, the test verifies that the message that goes to SAP has new fields that are not published to any other app but to SAP.
Test_Step_Description:
EDI:
Create and upload 2 EDIs - one interchange and one rev settlement - to add a new junction with either origin or destination station as a CP station with all required fields with following
i. JCT05, JCT07, JCT07, JCT09
ii. JS01, JS02, JS03, JS04 - (Interchange wll have these fields as null and Rev settlement will have values)
iii. DTM01, DTM02, DTM03
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The EDIs should be visible in Mercator web tool (B2B: Transaction 437)
