Test_Step_Description: Verify the Tgt message published to SAP
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The Tgt messages to SAP should be identical to Src messages

Test_Case_Name: UR8-TC11-Expire a junction interchange and settlement that has atleast one station as a CP-station
Description: The test verifies that an IRF message with interchange details is published to SAP when an EDI to expire an interchange or a settlement on an interchange that has atleast one stations (origin or destination) as a CPRS station, is processed. Also, the test verifies that the message that goes to SAP has new fields that are not published to any other app but to SAP.
Test_Step_Description: Verify the messages published to other Tgts
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The messages should not have the new fields

Test_Case_Name: UR7-TC15-Freight train movement events are not published to SAP
Description:
The test verifies that the freight 
train movement events that are published to TRIEX, OCS and TYES are not published 
to SAP. Only BULK/UNIT train movement events are published to SAP
Test_Step_Description:
Nexus, TYES, ITM:
Add a freight train to plan, build 
the train in TYES and depart and arrive the train at few stations
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The MTP events ACTOMTS should be triggered 
by tsz_169 program

Test_Case_Name: UR7-TC15-Freight train movement events are not published to SAP
Description:
The test verifies that the freight 
train movement events that are published to TRIEX, OCS and TYES are not published 
to SAP. Only BULK/UNIT train movement events are published to SAP
Test_Step_Description:
Verify the queue XI.TSD_TRAIN_MVMNT.RECEIVE.01 
for the train movement message
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The train movement events for freight 
train should not be published to SAP and hence there should be no messages in 
the queue.

Description: Outbound a train in TYES and send DFLC events to EME.
Test_Step_Description: After a train has been built in TYES and waybills exist for all equipment on the train then manually outbound the train.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The train will show as successfully outbounded in TYES. The train will move from the built train queue to the outbounded train queue on the outbound console in TYES. For each of the cars on the train, a DFLC event will be created which can be viewed in the TYES Last Moves screen. These DFLC events will be published to EME.

Description: Outbound a train in TYES and send DFLC events to EME.
Test_Step_Description: Verify that departure events have arrived EME and are stored in the database.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The DFLC events for all the equipment on the outbounded train will be stored in the EME tables
eqpmv_rfeqp_mvmnt_event and eqpmv_last_lctn_prcs with a timestamp corresponding to the time that the train was outbound in TYES.

This can be verified by running the Link Query to capture all the events for the car.

Description: Change the event date/time for an event previously stored in EME
Test_Step_Description: Bring up the EME events for a car.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: All the events in EME should be displayed on the EME corrections screen for the equipment initial and number that was entered.

Description: Change the event date/time for an event previously stored in EME
Test_Step_Description: Change the event date/time for the last event for the equipment and save the changes.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The changes made will show as successfully saved in the EME corrections application.

Description: Change the event date/time for an event previously stored in EME
Test_Step_Description: Verify that event date/time has been updated in the database.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The event that was changed in EME Correction should show the new event date/time in both eqpmv_rfeqp_mvmnt_event and eqpmv_last_lctn_prcs.

This can be verified by running the Link Query to capture all the events for the car.

Description:
Objectives :
In the save operation, the STCC codes will be associated with one/more of special handling process codes for a particular date range and saved into the database

Pre-condition :
1. User should have authenticate access for this functionality of the application.
2. The user should take care to enter only the STCC codes which are not already associated with any of the special handling process for the duration which the user intends to use
Test_Step_Description:
If user wants to save a single STCC code, the following are the ways to achieve it. User can enter the value with any of the below said combination.

i. Enter the required STCC code in the FROM STCC textbox and leave the TO STCC textbox empty and leaving the multiple STCC field i.e "Enter >1 single STCC codes" textbox empty.
        i.e:  FROM STCC = 4848400
              TO STCC = BLANK
              Multiple STCC = BLANK
ii. Enter the required STCC code in the FROM STCC and the same in the TO STCC field leaving the multiple STCC field i.e "Enter >1 single STCC codes" textbox empty.
        i.e:  FROM STCC = 4848400 
              TO STCC = 4848400 
              Multiple STCC = BLANK
iii. Enter the single STCC code in the multiple STCC textbox i.e "Enter >1 single STCC codes" textbox. Then leaving the FROM STCC and TO STCC fields as blank
       i.e:  Multiple STCC = 4848400
             FROM STCC = BLANK 
             TO STCC = BLANK
Test_Step_Expected_Result: User successfully able to enter the value in "From STCC" , "To STCC" .

 i.e: FROM STCC = 4848400 and

              TO STCC = BLANK
              Multiple STCC = BLANK
ii. Enter the required STCC code in the FROM STCC and the same in the TO STCC field leaving the multiple STCC field i.e "Enter >1 single STCC codes" textbox empty.
        i.e:  FROM STCC = 4848400 
              TO STCC = 4848400 
              Multiple STCC = BLANK
iii. Enter the single STCC code in the multiple STCC textbox i.e "Enter >1 single STCC codes" textbox. Then leaving the FROM STCC and TO STCC fields as blank
       i.e:  Multiple STCC = 4848400
             FROM STCC = BLANK 
             TO STCC = BLANK

Test_Case_Name: Refresh with new Inspections and new Elements

Login to EMU acpt: http://emuvsrva/EquipmentManagementUtility
 Click 'EMIS' and go to Error List page
Test_Step_Expected_Result: There should be no errors for the message

Test_Case_Name: Refresh with new Inspections and new Elements
Test_Step_Description:
Login to ORAA02 and extract the EQPMNT_ID from EQPMNT_AAR_BASE substitute in following query. 

SELECT efra.CRTFD_BY,
efra.CNDCTD_BY,
emwi.CMPLTD_TMS,
efra.INSPCT_DUE_DT,
emwi.PRFRMD_BY_MARK_CD,
emwi.RPRTD_BY_SCAC_CD,
efra.SCHDLD_DUE_DT,
emwi.SPLC_CD,
los.OOS_FROM_TMS,
los.OOS_TO_TMS,
los.OOS_NBR_DAYS
FROM EQPMNT_MNTNC_WORK_ITEM emwi,
 EQPMNT_ASGNMN_AAR eaa
  ,
 LCM_FRA_INSPCT efra
  ,
 LCM_OUT_OF_SRVC los
WHERE EAA.EQPMNT_ID = <equipment id>
          
AND 
eaa.WORK_ITEM_ID  
= 
emwi.WORK_ITEM_ID 
          
AND 
emwi.TRNSCT_CD    
IN ( 
'AFM','FRA','FRQ','FRY','ERI','HBI','LOA','LTA','OSI','LAC')
          
AND 
efra.WORK_ITEM_ID 
= 
eaa.WORK_ITEM_ID
          
AND 
los.WORK_ITEM_ID 
= 
emwi.WORK_ITEM_ID
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Query should return 10 rows - one for each inspection

Description: This tests the MQs involved in locomotive planned movement events from ITM/LMS to SADB-LMS
Test_Step_Description: Login to ITM and assign one or more locos to a train in 'Locomotive Planning' window
Test_Step_Expected_Result: This should send plan message to SADB-LMS

Description: This tests the MQs involved in locomotive planned movement events from ITM/LMS to SADB-LMS
Test_Step_Description:
Validate
- MQ LS.PROD.SUBSCRIBE.03
- lsz003 logs
- LCMTV_MVMNT_PLAN_EVENT table
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
- MQ LS.PROD.SUBSCRIBE.03 should receive the plan message from LMS
- lsz003 audit log should confirm the successful processing of the message and publishing of the data to following 
queues.
UT.TSD.NOTIFY.PUB01
UT.TSD.NOTIFY.PUB02
lsz003 error log should show no errors for this message. Note that audi log shows only the lead loco information.

Note: If the loco is assigned only to the rear position, the log may not mention it. This is as-is and is okay for this 
project.
- LCMTV_MVMNT_PLAN_EVENT table should be updated with records for the planned events with correct data

Description: This tests the MQs involved in locomotive planned movement events from ITM/LMS to SADB-LMS

Validate
- MQs UT.TSD.NOTIFY.PUB01 and UT.TSD.NOTIFY.PUB02
- TSZ169 logs
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
- MQs UT.TSD.NOTIFY.PUB01 and UT.TSD.NOTIFY.PUB02 should receive the messages from lsz003
- tsz169 has two audit logs, one for each queue. Both audit logs should confirm the successful processing of the 
messages from SADB-LMS. Error log should have no errors for this message.

Test_Step_Description:

This should be done by the OASIS business user.

Check the audit and debug log of the EME program eez008 and verify Track list request message is processed 
successfully.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Audit and debug log of the program should have Track list request message data.

Test_Step_Description:
Check the error log of the program eez008 and check if any error log record is created for the Track list request 
message
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Error log of the program eez003 should not have any error log record for the Track list request message.

Test_Step_Description:
Check the audit and debug log of the EME program eez008 and verify Track list reply message is generated 
successfully.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Track list reply message should be generated successfully

Test_Step_Description:
Confirm with the OASIS business user Track list reply message triggered by EME successfully reached OASIS and 
processed successfully.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Track list reply message should be processed successfully at OASIS
Reply should be received by OASIS successfully.

Trigger the EME_REQUEST message at the OASIS application.
This should be done by the OASIS business user.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: EME_REQUEST message should be successfully triggered by the OASIS business user.

Test_Step_Description:
Check the audit and debug log of the EME program eez003 and verify EME_REQUEST 
message is processed successfully.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Audit and debug log of the program should have EME_REQUEST message data.

Test_Step_Description:
Check the error log of the program eez003 and check if any error log record is created for the 
EME_REQUEST message
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
Error log of the program eez003 should not have any error log record for the EME_REQUEST 
message.

Test_Step_Description:
Check the audit and debug log of the EME program eez003 and verify EME_REPLY message is 
generated successfully.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: EME_REPLY message should be generated successfully

Test_Step_Description:
Confirm with the OASIS business user EME_REPLY message triggered by EME successfully 
reached OASIS and processed successfully.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: EME_REPLY message should be processed successfully at OASIS
Reply should be received by OASIS successfully.

valid values. along with other existing required elements.

Railinc

Description:
Description - To validate if  the EME Script EET031 runs sucessfully.

Pre-condition - Failed interchange errors available in DB.

Post Condition -  Updates the table emeapp_failed_msg_hndlng
Test_Step_Description:
Verify if failed data available in the DB using the below query.

  SELECT * FROM emeapp_failed_msg_hndlng hndlng,                                                           
               emeapp_failed_msg        msg,
               emeapp_failed_msg_eqpmt  eqpmt,
               cntl_task_msg_log_rfrnc  rfrnc
         WHERE hndlng.msg_tag_txt = 'TYES_INTRCH'
           AND hndlng.msg_status_cd in ('RETRY', 'FAILED')
           AND hndlng.failed_msg_hndlng_id   = msg.failed_msg_hndlng_id
           AND msg.failed_msg_vrsn_id        = eqpmt.failed_msg_vrsn_id
           AND eqpmt.msg_state_cd            =  'ACTIVE'
           AND hndlng.failed_msg_hndlng_id   = msg.failed_msg_hndlng_id
           AND msg.failed_msg_vrsn_id        = eqpmt.failed_msg_vrsn_id
           AND eqpmt.task_msg_log_id         = rfrnc.task_msg_log_id 
           ORDER BY eqpmt.failed_msg_vrsn_id,    eqpmt.record_create_tms;
Test_Step_Expected_Result: Data should be available in the table.

Description:
Description - To validate if  the EME Script EET036 runs sucessfully.

Pre-condition - 

Post Condition -  Updates the table
Test_Step_Description:
SELECT * FROM
eqpmv_last_lctn_prcs     last_lctn,
            eqpmv_eqpmt_event_type   event_type,
            eqpmv_bad_order          bad_order 
   WHERE last_lctn.bad_order_edi_event_cd IS NOT NULL
   AND last_lctn.bad_order_event_type_id = event_type.eqpmt_event_type_id
            AND last_lctn.bad_order_event_id      = bad_order.event_id
            AND last_lctn.off_line_cd             = 'Y'
            AND last_lctn.eqpun_type_cd           IN ('I','O')
            AND bad_order.source_system_nm        IN ('BAD_ORDER','CIM');

Pre-condition - 1) The programs eez001, eez015, eez033 and eez034 should be triggered ON at EME.

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to EME DB.

Data Requirements - The TYES_TRKMV_UPD message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description: Trigger ON the MQ EE.CIT.SUBSCRIBE.01 by using the option 7 - Set trigger control of the MQ util facility.
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The MQ should be triggered ON.

Description:
Description - To verify if the TYES_TRKMV_UPD message is getting processed in the same way in new acceptance as it is processed in old acceptance.

Post-condition - 1) Message should be passed to EME DB.

Data Requirements - The TYES_TRKMV_UPD message should have valid data.
Test_Step_Description:
Log into EME Unix application and check the audit log of the program eez033 in the location  /acpt/eme/bin/eez_33
Check the following parameters in the audit log.
1) Time Stamp.
2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez033 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be EME_TRKMV
After successful processing of EME_TRKMV message EME_TRKMV_CHG message should be created.

Test_Step_Description:

2) Message tag.
Test_Step_Expected_Result:
The messages should reach EME application and the log should be created for the newly received message.
The message should be successfully processed by the eez001 program.
Value of the parameters should be :-
1) Time Stamp - should be latest
2) Message tag should be TRAIN
After successful processing of TRAIN message, TRAIN message should be created.

Test_Step_Description: Login to ORAA02 and query EQPMNT_AAR_BASE table for the equipment added
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The record for the equipment should exist and DLTD_TMS should be NULL

Test_Case_Name: ECA with new elements and valid element values
Test_Step_Description:
Run the below query
SELECT DISTINCT
         D.AAR_ELMNT_ID,
            A.CMPNT_NM
         || '_'
         || B.CMPNT_LCTN_CD
         || '_'
         || REPLACE (D.ELMNT_NM, ' ', '_')
            FIELD_NAME,
         c.VALUE_TXT
    FROM EQPMNT_CMPNT A,
         EQPMNT_CMPNT_ASCTN B,
         EQPMNT_CMPNT_ELMNT_ASCTN C,
         INFO_DATA_ELMNT D,
         eqpmnt_aar_base e
   WHERE     A.CMPNT_ID = B.CMPNT_ID
         AND B.EQPMNT_CMPNT_ASCTN_ID = C.EQPMNT_CMPNT_ASCTN_ID
         AND C.INFO_DATA_ELMNT_ID = D.INFO_DATA_ELMNT_ID
         AND B.EQPMNT_ID = E.EQPMNT_ID
         AND E.MARK_CD = 'RAIL'
         AND E.EQPUN_NBR = 226
ORDER BY FIELD_NAME;
Test_Step_Expected_Result: The new elements for the equipment should exist
